{{distinguish|Joseph Brady (soccer)}} {{more citations needed|date=March 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Joe Brady | image = | caption = | fullname = Joseph Brady | birth_date = 18xx | birth_place = Unknown | death_date = 19xx | death_place = | height = | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = | clubs1 = [[Renton F.C.|Renton]] | years2 = 1892–1893 | clubs2 = [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = }}'''Joseph 'Joe' Brady''' was a [[Association football|footballer]] who played as an [[Midfielder|outside left or right]] for [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] during the [[1892–93 Sheffield United F.C. season|1892–93 season]].<ref name="blades whos who">{{cite book |author=Denis Clarebrough & Andrew Kirkham |title=Sheffield United Who's Who |publisher=Hallamshire Press |year=2008|page=63 |isbn=978-1-874718-69-7}}</ref> Registered at the start of the club's first campaign in [[The Football League]] he struggled to break into the first team and made only ten appearances in total during the course of the season, although most of these were in friendlies.<ref name="blades whos who" /> His only competitive games were against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] in the [[Northern Football League|Northern League]] and against [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] in the [[FA Cup]].<ref name="blades whos who" /> Lacking the quality needed to play in the Football League he was released in the summer of 1893.<ref name="blades whos who" />
